                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13446766" author="amilam" created="Sat, 1 Sep 2012 17:48:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Locks are acquired via the VFSUtils#acquireLock() method. This has the following method.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;String fullPath = fo.getURL().toString();&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This getURL() method always creates a Java URL class object and return it. But the Java URL class separates the url if there is a # and considers the rest of the url as a reference part (see the URL.java).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But instead of this, we can use&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;String fullPath = fo.getName().getURI(); which returns the correct URI. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13446767" author="amilam" created="Sat, 1 Sep 2012 17:49:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching the patch for this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13714072" author="hiranya" created="Fri, 19 Jul 2013 21:06:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch applied. Thanks Amila for the contribution.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
